I"N<p>Dr Kilannin Krysiak joined the lab as a staff scientist and then was promoted to Instructor of Medicine. She led a number of projects, making very important contributions to CIViC and a number of lymphoma studies. She will embark on the next stage of her career by joining the prestigious <a href="http://www.abmgg.org/pages/training_options.shtml">ABMGG</a>-accredited <a href="https://pathology.wustl.edu/training/clinical-fellowships/laboratory-genetics-and-genomics-fellowship/">Laboratory Genetics and Genomics (LGG) fellowship at Washington University School of Medicine</a>.</p>

